org.societies.android.api.cis
Class SocialContract.Membership

java.lang.Object

Enclosing class:
SocialContract
public static final class SocialContract.Membership
extends java.lang.Object


Constants and helpers for operating on memberships in communities.

This is the URI you will use for accessing information about who is member in which community. Every membership which is accessible from this user's SocialProvider has an entry in this table. You can find information about both of the following:

  • Which communities a user is a member of.
  • Which members a community has.
  • Which types of membership a user has in a community.
You might have different levels of information for the different memberships based on your access rights to services that provide this information.

Insert

Applications can insert memberships. Applications will have to provide the following parameters in when inserting memberships:
  • GLOBAL_ID_MEMBER
  • GLOBAL_ID_COMMUNITY
  • TYPE
  • ORIGIN
When an application inserts a membership, SYNC_STATUS will be set to "pending" by SocialProvider. This has to be changed by a SyncAdapter upon next successful synchronization. SyncAdapters can also insert services. SyncAdapters have to set the following parameters in the query in order to insert successfully:
  • GLOBAL_ID
  • GLOBAL_ID_MEMBER
  • GLOBAL_ID_COMMUNITY
  • TYPE
  • ORIGIN
SYNC_STATUS has to be set to "updated" by the SyncAdapter.

Update

Applications can update:
  • TYPE
SyncAdapters can update:
  • TYPE
SYNC_STATUS has to be set to "updated" by the SyncAdapter.

Delete

Applications can delete memberships. A user (and his/her logged in application) can delete the following memberships:
  • Memberships that involve the user.
  • Memberships that involve communities where the user is owner.

SyncAdapters can delete any membership.

Query

Applications and SyncAdapters can query for memberships using standard query URI or using _ID as the last part of the URI.
